thread.title: exporting

comments.text: you can export creations and areas to *.obj files for further use elsewhere, like in 3d modeling programs.
to export a thing of yours (or one made clonable by someone else), context-laser it and turn around the thing dialog. the back has an export button.
to export a whole area made by you (or made copyable by someone else), open the area (mountain icon) dialog and turn it around. an export button shows there too.
at anyland.com/info/thing-format.html you can also find out a bit more on the json data structure that comes with thing exports.
